{"TopicId":126858,"ForumId":46,"TopicTitle":"Include Quotes While Editing Posts?","CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T10:14:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T10:14:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, the new editor is crashing a lot for me - leaving malformed posts with no content.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRather than double posting, am I able to insert a quote into an edit of a post? I have the little multi-quote window in the bottom-right corner of the screen - but do not see any way to insert it into a post.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne more problem, half the time I am submitting a new post, it seems to be lost and not posted (along with everything I spent time writing).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUsing Google Chrome Version\u00A046.0.2490.86 m, no plugins.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022970a7b0aec.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://puu.sh/lGu59/970a7b0aec.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-02T10:15:56Z\u0022 title=\u002212/02/2015 10:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 2, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Beale\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T11:04:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is (supposed to be) a button. You click it and it inserts the quotes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf that doesn\u0027t work it\u0027s just another bug you\u0027re experiencing \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T11:06:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222304437\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449054271\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is (supposed to be) a button. You click it and it inserts the quotes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf that doesn\u0027t work it\u0027s just another bug you\u0027re experiencing \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSadly doesn\u0027t work. When I click the button, it tries to put the quotes in a new post, not the post I am editing. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Val","CreatedById":126227,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T11:18:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCopy-paste of quotes don\u0027t work in Chrome. I have to use Edge or IE to manipulate quotes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beale","CreatedById":70533,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T17:35:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222304450\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449055129\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCopy-paste of quotes don\u0027t work in Chrome. I have to use Edge or IE to manipulate quotes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the answer!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough it is really not a nice answer to hear \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WinkAllKerb\u0026#039;\u0026#039;","CreatedById":78047,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T17:41:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nprobably doable in 2 edits, first edit, then start a new post with quote, copy paste \u0026amp; don\u0027t validate the new post, reedit your post and paste the quote.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-02T17:41:46Z\u0022 title=\u002212/02/2015 05:41  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 2, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by WinkAllKerb\u0026#039;\u0026#039;\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hobbes Novakoff","CreatedById":129018,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T17:58:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPasting quotes works for me in Safari.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"WinkAllKerb\u0026#039;\u0026#039;","CreatedById":78047,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T18:25:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanyway chrome thing might has something to do with NPAPI java thing i guess no ? or may be it\u0027s related either with OS and 32 or 64 version also, dunno.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.java.com/fr/download/faq/chrome.xml\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.java.com/fr/download/faq/chrome.xml\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:9px;\u0022\u003Ebut my own bet is it\u00A0still work with the two step edit as a workaround ; )\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222304450\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449055129\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022126227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Val\u0022 style=\u0022margin:0px;padding:0px 15px;border-width:1px 1px 1px 2px;border-style:solid;clear:both;color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:22.4px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background:rgb(251,251,251);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022 style=\u0022margin:0px -15px;padding:5px 15px;color:rgb(34,34,34);font-weight:bold;font-size:13px;background:rgb(243,243,243);\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Val said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCopy-paste of quotes \u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:line-through;\u0022\u003Edon\u0027t\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#008000;\u0022\u003Emay\u003C/span\u003E work in Chrome. I have to use Edge or IE to manipulate quotes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;f